name: Mother Nature Strikes Back!
tweet: My Mother died from Ovarian Cancer at 84.  Many advances have been made in testing for familial genetic propensity to breast and ovarian cancer.  CA125 blood tests are used yearly in some cancer cases.  But seeing young women with ovarian cancer at the oncologist?  Tough to see.
